Robot-assisted spelling. See [[User:Mathbot/Logged misspellings]] for changes.
/* Properties */ The faces are in general chiral, but the parallelepiped is not.
Each face is, seen from the outside, the mirror image of the opposite face.;  two adjacent ones are equal and the other two also, both being the mirror image of the first two.
Parallelepipeds with a symmetry plane either have four rectangular faces, or two rhombic faces, while the faces of one of the other pairs are the mirror image of the faces of the third pair.
/* Properties */ Parallelepipeds with a symmetry plane either have four rectangular faces, or two rhombic faces and four equal ones. See also [[monoclinic]].
[[Tessellation of space]] is possible with congruent copies of any parallelepiped.
Space can be filled with equal copies of any parallelepiped.
a '''parallelepiped''' or '''parallelopipedon''' is a [[prism (geometry)|prism]] of which the base is a [[parallelogram]], in other words, a [[polyhedron]] with six faces, each a parallelogram.
